commit.message: Tests: Make sure file names of optimization tests clearly indicate they are tests
Fix, writing XML tree output could fail with encoding errors
Anti-Bloat: Recognize "keras" testing modules as unittest bloat
Quality: Fix, isort and black can corrupt outputs, catch that

Minor cleanups

* A bit of spelling, and the template expansion can of course do the ".cache" suffix already.
Minor cleanup
Python3.12: This function also needs to be fully migrated

Optimization: Have dedicated helper for "list.remove"

* Avoids making an API call that is slow on Windows

* Avoids in-place list assignment overhead of Python and allows for simpler code generation.
Python3.12: Cleanup, with this name error code it should be easier
fixup! Debugging: Generate Scons Pipeline Debug Script
Python3.12: Workaround for "_PyStaticType_GetState" not being exported
Python3.12: Added "Nuitka_LongSetSign" variant too
Python3.12: Adaptations for "unicode" objects to be always ready

Python3.12: Changes for current exception to be only value

* When saving and restoring, use a structure, such that 3 or 1 value becomes transparent.

* When raising exceptions from helper code, do not use 3 value restore form, but dedicated helpers instead.

* Asserting unchanged exception state is now done with helpers too.

Optimization: Recognize exact type shapes of loops

* This enables appends to list to be optimized to their dedicated nodes among other things
Added TODO for set operations in variables
Optimization: Lower "in" tests in "set" and list objects to "frozenset" and "tuple" respectively
Optimization: Use set specific API for in tests in set/frozenset values
Merge tag '2.1.4' into develop
Merge branch 'hotfix/2.1.4'
New hotfix release.
Standalone: Added support for newer "tensorflow" package
Anti-Bloat: Avoid compiling tensorflow testing code
Optimization: Avoid recompiling "azure" which is not performance relevant

Python2: Need to do encoding manual and save as bytes

* Otherwise we were trying to encode for no good reason and failing at that potentially
Standalone: Fix, matplotlib needs emit dependency on the backend.
Plugins: Use "plugin" warnings for GUI plugins to be used
Anti-Bloat: Avoid "setuptools" in deepspeed package
Plugins: Remove obsolete plugins from this document.

Onefile: Respect "XDG_CACHE_HOME" variable (Merges: 2791)

*  When rendering "{CACHE_DIR}" path specs on non-Windows this should
   be used if set.

*  Uses "$XDG_CACHE_HOME" as base for "{CACHE_DIR}" if it is present,
   and absolute path, falling back to the current default of "~/.cache"
   only if not.
